<title>GERMANY: Thyssen spins off peripheral units.</title>
<headline>Thyssen spins off peripheral units.</headline>
<dateline>ESSEN, Germany 1997-02-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Thyssen Industrie AG said on Wednesday it had sold two peripheral subsidiaries as part of a restructuring to concentrate on core activities.</p>
<p>The unit of steel and engineering group Thyssen AG said it has sold a ring-rolling plant construction unit to Eumuco Hasenclever GmbH of Leverkusen. That transaction has already been approved by cartel authorities.</p>
<p>It also sold its Ruhrpumpen pump unit to the Canadian-Mexican Derlan Industries EG.</p>
<p>Thyssen said the new owners would continue operations of the plants in Witten, preserving 210 jobs.</p>
<p>-- Terence Gallagher, Bonn newsroom, 49-228-26097150</p>
